I always say... 

When #python is still struggling with a decent dataframe #RStats is using nested data frame...

R has a 100 problems but not been able to work in #datascience is not one them... It's in fact the opposite, we face issue while integrating it on web.

@gvarnu @nicoforteza1 @nickchk I agree that deployment in #RStats is a hassle. Specially if you are not working on RStudio products... You have to write almost everything by hand... Which is hard and frustrating...

But I never ever found any issues with debugging on @rstudio.

@JohnDCook @MapleTaffyCap @RHDZMOTA @ephorie And my situation is in fact end to end data science... That #Rstats is excellent at... Only 1 out of a 50 cases you would wish you had something more available... Rest R handles pretty fine.

@Imy3648 @haifabmes @rstatstweet You may absolutely be right... Most people started learning #python because of job requirements... I don't use it much but I have it in my resume just to say that yes I know it 😏...

#RStats jobs are mostly regarding analysis while #python jobs are about development... So true

@MapleTaffyCap @haifabmes @rstatstweet I know a few people who have over 12 years of experience in finance, forecasting etc
They always say #RStats is miles ahead of #python in terms of time series analysis, and financial stuff. They couldn't find appropriate methods that they need. But company forces them into python
